The U.K. government will start a 1
billion-pound ($1.6 billion) program to fund  carbon capture  and
storage projects during the parliamentary recess.  The competition for the technology that gathers emissions
for permanent storage underground will open during the break,
which starts today and ends April 16, Secretary of State for
Energy and Climate Change Ed Davey wrote in a statement on his
